			<ns0:name>halya...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112856509894568708731/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">There is no security concern here anymore. But we still need to fix a crash. It happens when new thread starts and GS value is changed to non-zero due to this windows bug. This non-zero value then remembered in a trusted context structure. When untrusted code calls trusted, this invalid value is extracted from the trusted context and is written to GS. If the GS selector is invalid at this time, NaCl crashes.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2011-05-13T06:10:03.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2011-05-13T06:10:03.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 4 by halya...@google.com</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=1800#c4" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/1800/comments/full/4" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>